<subSubSection pageId="117" pageNumber="513" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="117.[115,1321,2772,3474]" pageId="117" pageNumber="513">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[117,472,3327,3356]" pageId="117" pageNumber="513">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. MacArthur’s White-toothed Shrew is considered rare within its broad but seemingly fragmented distribution. The species is found in the Meru National Park in Kenya and may be threatened by habitat destruction due to agricultural expansion.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
